# Base Operations Rules

## Runtime Reliability

- Define sane timeouts for network and I/O operations.
- Use retries only with bounded policy and clear stop conditions.
- Prefer idempotent behavior for retryable commands/jobs.

## Observability Baseline

- Ensure critical flows emit logs with correlation/trace context.
- Track failures and latency with metrics where practical.
- Never log secrets or raw sensitive payloads.

## Health And Readiness

- Expose or document health/readiness checks for deployable services.
- Verify startup configuration errors fail fast and clearly.

## Rollout And Rollback

- For behavior-impacting changes, define rollback steps before release.
- Document toggles/flags and safe fallback path when applicable.
